parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To take note of, perceive, consider carefully, discern, detect, make account of. From kata and noieo; to observe fully.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A raven, crow. Perhaps from korennumi; a crow.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To sow, spread, scatter. Probably strengthened from spao; to scatter, i.e. Sow.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To reap, gather, harvest. From theros; to harvest.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Dative Masculine Plural
str2: Who, which, what, that.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
A store-chamber, secret chamber, closet; a granary, barn.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
A repository, granary, barn, storehouse. From apotithemi; a repository, i.e. Granary.
And, even, also, namely.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A primary verb; properly, to stiffen, i.e. Fatten (with food, etc.), pamper, rear).

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Dative Neuter Singular
str2: How much, how great, how many. From an absolute pos and hos; interrogative pronoun how much (plural) many).
More, rather. Neuter of the comparative of the same as malista; more) or rather.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: From dia and phero; to bear through, i.e. transport; usually to bear apart, i.e. to toss about; subjectively, to 'differ', or surpass.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A bird, fowl. Neuter of a derivative of petomai; a flying animal, i.e. Bird.
